## Technical Specifications

- Data Models (Schema Details)
  - ContentItem
    - id: string
    - title: string
    - slug?: string
    - projectId: string
    - status: "idea" | "research" | "draft" | "edit" | "ready-to-publish" | "published"
    - authorId: string
    - assigneeIds: string[]
    - calendarItem?: { start: string; end?: string; allDay?: boolean }
    - scheduledAt?: string
    - publishedAt?: string
    - version: number
    - seoKeywords: string[]
    - performanceMetrics?: { views?: number; ctr?: number; avgPosition?: number }
    - createdAt: string
    - updatedAt: string
  - CronJob
    - id: string
    - name: string
    - enabled: boolean
    - scheduleCron?: string
    - timezone: string
    - triggerType: "time" | "event" | "conditional"
    - targetAgentId?: string
    - inputPayload: any
    - permissions: "suggest-only" | "approval-required" | "conditional-auto" | "bounded-autopilot"
    - constraints: { maxActions?: number; spendLimit?: number; allowedTools?: string[] }
    - safetyRails: { confirmationsRequired?: boolean; approvalsNeeded?: string[] }
    - retryPolicy: { maxRetries?: number; backoffMs?: number; deadLetterQueue?: string }
    - outputs: { runHistory?: string[]; logs?: string[]; artifacts?: string[] }
    - createdAt: string
    - updatedAt: string
  - RunArtifact
    - id: string
    - cronJobId: string
    - status: "queued" | "running" | "success" | "failed" | "skipped"
    - startedAt: string
    - finishedAt?: string
    - artifacts: any
    - logs: string[]
    - diffs?: string
  - SEOInsight
    - id: string
    - contentItemId: string
    - keyword: string
    - searchVolume: number
    - difficulty: number
    - suggestedTitle: string
    - metaDescription: string
  - AgentRecommendation
    - id: string
    - topic: string
    - rationale: string
    - confidence: number

- API Endpoints (Routes and Methods)
  - GET /api/content/items?filters&page&limit&search
  - GET /api/content/item/{id}
  - POST /api/content/item
  - PUT /api/content/item/{id} (update fields like status, scheduledAt, assignees, etc.)
  - GET /api/cronjobs
  - POST /api/cronjobs
  - PUT /api/cronjobs/{id}
  - GET /api/analytics/seo?contentItemId=
  - GET /api/analytics/performance?contentItemId=
  - GET /api/audit/run/{runId}
  - GET /api/agents/recommendations
  - POST /api/editor/open (open Content Editor with starter data)
  - POST /api/cronjobs/{id}/run (force/run now)
  - PATCH /api/content/item/{id}/advance (move to next stage)
  - PATCH /api/content/calendar/{id}/move (update scheduling)

- Security
  - JWT/OIDC authentication; role-based access control:
    - Admin, Editor, Approver, Viewer
  - All endpoints validate authentication, authorization, input schemas, and rate limits
  - Sensitive actions (approve, publish, schedule changes) require appropriate permissions and audits
  - All actions emit a traceable audit record with userId, timestamp, action, and diffs

- Validation
  - Use runtime validation on all inputs (e.g., Zod or Yup) with defaults
  - All fetch results pass through validators; default to [] when arrays are missing
  - Date/time fields are ISO 8601 strings and timezone-aware where needed

- Safety & Nullability Rules (enforced throughout)
  - data ?? [] for array results
  - (items ?? []).map(...) and Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - useState<Type[]>([]) initializations
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Optional chaining for nested fields
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

