## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] The Content Dashboard renders without runtime errors on initial load, with all panels displaying data from the APIs and safe guards in place for nulls.
- [ ] All array operations guard against null/undefined values using the runtime safety patterns outlined.
- [ ] Drag-and-drop on ContentCalendarPanel updates scheduling correctly, triggers a CronJob update, and logs an audit trail.
- [ ] DraftsPanel supports stage advancement and approvals workflow; status transitions reflect in PublishingQueuePanel and audit logs.
- [ ] PublishingQueuePanel shows accurate nextRun times, statuses, and outcomes; retry logic is visible and functional.
- [ ] SEOPerformancePanel surfaces at least 3 keyword recommendations with measurable metrics and a CTA to open Editor with the item preloaded.
- [ ] Global Search returns accurate results across projects, content, cronjobs, runs, and users; filters update as expected.
- [ ] Content Editor shortcut opens with an end-to-end flow initialized for a given ContentItem or a new idea; versioning is tracked.
- [ ] All API responses validate shapes; responses with missing fields are sanitized to safe defaults.
- [ ] UI interactions are accessible (keyboard navigation, ARIA labels) and responsive.

