## Content Dashboard

## Overview
Build a comprehensive Content Dashboard for LifeOps that provides an at-a-glance overview of content pipelines. The page surfaces:
- Content Calendar with drag-to-reschedule
- Drafts in progress with status stages (idea, research, draft, edit, ready to publish)
- Publishing status queue and per-post progress
- Pending approvals queue
- SEO/performance insights and optimization suggestions
- Quick access to the connected Content Editor for end-to-end ideation through publish
- Global and module-scoped search and filtering across projects, content, cronjobs, runs, and users
All components must be themed to the provided dark UI design system, accessible, and performant at scale. Include robust audit/log artifacts for every action.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)

What this page is:
- The Content Dashboard is the central overview for content pipelines within LifeOps. It aggregates data from content ideas, research tasks, drafts, scheduled publications, and analytics to give operators a holistic view of content health, throughput, and ROI. It also serves as the launcher to the Content Editor and to automation tooling for ideation, drafting, editing, and publishing through LLM-assisted pipelines and publishing connectors.

Goals:
- Provide a real-time (or near-real-time) overview of content lifecycle stages and bottlenecks.
- Surface SEO and performance indicators with actionable recommendations.
- Facilitate end-to-end content automation orchestration (via the Content Pipeline Automation feature).
- Enable efficient search and filtering across multiple domains: projects, content items, cronjobs, runs, users.
- Offer a safe, auditable environment with full run artifacts, reversion capabilities, and human-in-the-loop controls.

Connected features and UI guidance:
- Content Calendar: Interactive calendar grid showing scheduled content, with drag-and-drop to reschedule. Dragging should update the underlying cron/job scheduling in a safe, auditable way and reflect in the per-run history.
- Drafts Panel: Card- or list-based view showing items in stages (idea, research, draft, edit). Each item shows title, author, stage, ETA, assigned agents, and quick actions (move to next stage, escalate, request approvals).
- Publishing Queue: A queue/list of posts scheduled for publishing with target channels (publish connectors). Show status, next publish time, retries, and outcome history.
- Agent Recommendations: A panel suggesting topics, outlines, and promotional ideas based on research corpora and real-time trend signals.
- SEO/Performance Widgets: Keyword suggestions, search volume estimates, traffic projections, ranking deltas, and on-page optimization hints.
- Search & Filter: Global search box and module-scoped search fields. Filters across projects, content, cronjobs, runs, users. Use multi-select facets, date ranges, status pills, and tag filters.
- Content Editor (Connected Page): A seamless entry point to the end-to-end editor with idea→research→draft→edit→schedule→publish flow, incorporating LLM-assisted writing, versioning, collaboration, and publishing integrations.
- API integrations: The page should not rely on external APIs in this prompt, but be designed to connect to a backend that exposes the required endpoints and data models.

UI/UX visual guidance (as per design specs):
- Dark UI with the supplied color palette, typography, spacings, and card design rules.
- Layout: Left navigation rail, top bar with global controls, and a responsive content area with a multi-column density-first layout that gracefully collapses on smaller viewports.
- Data visualization: Lightweight, accessible charts (e.g., KPI spark lines, trend charts) using the palette teal, amber, and purple for series accents.
- Interaction feedback: Subtle hover lifts, focus rings, and keyboard navigability. All actionable items must have clear affordances and reversible actions.

